  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Kamal & Ors. versus State of Gujarat & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_4_2736_2741','2025INSC504'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KAMAL & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF GUJARAT & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2736</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 504</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007352025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : MANOJ MISRA, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Appellants sought quashing of FIR in respect of offences u/ss.498-A and s.114 of IPC u/s.482 of CrPC. By the impugned order dated 01.02.2024, the High Court dismissed the petition. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.498-A and s.114 &ndash; Code of Criminal father-in-law and mother-in-law, respectively, of the second respondent &ndash; On 15.05.2019, the first appellant filed for divorce &ndash; On 20.07.2019, the second respondent lodged the impugned FIR &ndash; Appellants sought quashing of the impugned criminal proceedings &ndash; The High<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2042/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Partly allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_4_2736_2741','2025INSC504','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_4_2736_2741','2025INSC504',